toryError` if a file exists where a directory is expected. The return type is a frozen `SampleLibraryLayout` dataclass, which avoids the `self` keyword conflict by using `self_` for the field name while providing an `as_dict()` method for mapping back to on-disk names.\n+\n+## Completeness\n+The solution fully addresses the task requirements:\n+- Python function `create_sample_library_layout` implemented.\n+- Idempotent creation of the six specified subdirectories.\n+- Returns resolved paths in a dataclass.\n+- Comprehensive tests covering creation, idempotency, nested parent creation, and error cases (file-at-path).\n+- Documentation at `docs/cypherclaw-sample-directory-layout.md` accurately reflects the implementation.\n+\n+## Consistency\n+The implementation is consistent with the project's use of dataclasses and `pathlib.Path`. The placement in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_library.py` is appropriate given the related `SampleLibrary` and `SampleRecord` classes already residing there.\n+\n+## Security\n+No security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices identified. The directory creation uses safe `pathlib` methods.\n+\n+## Quality\n+The code quality is high, with clear docstrings and well-structured tests. The 16 tests in `tests/test_sample_library.py` pass successfully.\n+\n+## Issues Found\n+- [x] (Minor) Unrelated test failures in the full suite due to macOS Seatbelt restrictions on `~/.promptclaw/pets.json`, but the specific tests for T-027 passed in isolation and the core logic is verified.\n+\n+## Verdict: PASS\n+\n+## Notes for Lead Agent\n+The implementation of the directory creation helper is solid and follows all specifications. The use of `self_` in the dataclass to avoid keyword collision is a good choice. The `as_dict()` helper ensures that downstream consumers can still get the exact on-disk names easily."}
